
= RunPodFarm Scheduler =

#type:     node
#context:  top
#internal: runpodfarmscheduler
#icon:     TOP/scheduler

"""Schedules PDG work items on RunPod GPU Pods for distributed rendering and simulation."""

== Overview ==

This scheduler creates and manages a pool of RunPod GPU pods to execute PDG work items. Work items are distributed via a Redis queue, and results are collected through Redis and MQ.

The scheduler supports:
* Automatic pod pool management with configurable min/max pods
* Autoscaling based on queue depth and estimated remaining work
* Budget tracking with configurable cost limits
* Pod health monitoring via heartbeats
* Network volume support for shared storage

Before using the scheduler, you need:
* A RunPod account with API key
* A RunPod template (Docker image) with Houdini installed
* A Redis instance accessible from both your machine and RunPod pods
* Optionally, a RunPod Network Volume for shared storage

== Setup ==

# Install the `redis` Python package to `hython`:
    * `hython -m pip install redis`

# Restart Houdini to register the scheduler with PDG.

# Create a RunPod template with your Houdini Docker image.

# Set up a Redis instance (e.g., Redis Cloud, or self-hosted with TLS).

# Configure the scheduler parameters on the node.

== Using the Scheduler ==

# Enter the __API Key__, __GPU Type__, __Template ID__, and __Redis URL__ parameters.

# Set the __Min Pods__ and __Max Pods__ for your pod pool.

# Optionally configure __Max Cost__ to set a budget limit.

# Cook your TOP network. The scheduler will:
    * Create an initial pool of pods (Min Pods)
    * Distribute work items via Redis
    * Autoscale pods based on queue depth and estimated remaining time
    * Track costs and stop scaling if over budget
    * Terminate pods when the cook completes

=== Troubleshooting ===

* Ensure your Redis instance is accessible from both your local machine and RunPod pods. Use `rediss://` (TLS) URLs for production.

* If pods are not starting, check your RunPod API key, template ID, and GPU availability in the selected datacenter.

* Enable __Verbose Logging__ for detailed output to the Houdini console.

* If tasks are timing out, check that the pod worker script is correctly reading from the Redis task queue.

@parameters

== RunPod == (runpodparam)

Global parameters describing the RunPod configuration.

API Key:
    #id: rpfarm_apikey

    (Required) Your RunPod API key for authentication. Can be generated from the RunPod web console under Settings > API Keys.

GPU Type:
    #id: rpfarm_gputype

    The GPU model to request for pods. Examples: `NVIDIA RTX A6000`, `NVIDIA GeForce RTX 4090`, `NVIDIA A100 80GB PCIe`.

Template ID:
    #id: rpfarm_templateid

    (Required) The RunPod template ID defining the Docker image and configuration for pods. The template should include a Houdini installation and the pod worker script.

Network Volume ID:
    #id: rpfarm_networkvolumeid

    The RunPod Network Volume ID for shared storage between pods. The volume is mounted at `/workspace` inside the pod.

Datacenter:
    #id: rpfarm_datacenter

    Preferred RunPod datacenter region. Leave empty for automatic selection.

== Scaling == (scalingparam)

Parameters controlling pod pool autoscaling behavior.

Min Pods:
    #id: rpfarm_minpods

    Minimum number of pods to keep running during a cook. These pods are created at the start of the cook and maintained until completion.

Max Pods:
    #id: rpfarm_maxpods

    Maximum number of pods allowed. The autoscaler will not create more pods than this limit.

== Budget == (budgetparam)

Parameters controlling cost limits.

Max Cost ($):
    #id: rpfarm_maxcost

    Maximum allowed cost in USD for this cook. When the estimated cost reaches this limit, the scheduler stops creating new pods. Set to 0 for unlimited.

== Project == (projectparam)

Parameters identifying the project and Redis connection.

Redis URL:
    #id: rpfarm_redisurl

    (Required) The Redis connection URL. Supports `redis://` and `rediss://` (TLS) schemes. Example: `rediss://default:password@host:port`.

Project ID:
    #id: rpfarm_projectid

    Unique project identifier used to namespace Redis keys. This ensures multiple projects can share the same Redis instance without conflicts.

User ID:
    #id: rpfarm_userid

    User identifier for task queue namespacing.

=== Paths ===

Local Shared Path:
    #id: pdg_workingdir

    Specifies the root path on your local machine that points to the directory where the job generates intermediate files and output.

Remote Shared Path:
    #id: rpfarm_remoteworkingdir

    When enabled, overrides the path to the mounted directory on the RunPod pod. Typically `/workspace` when using Network Volumes.

