== Submit As Job ==
#id: submitgraph

    Allows you to schedule a standalone job (a job that __does not__ require Houdini to be running) on a RunPod pod that cooks the current TOP network.

Submit Graph As Job:
    #id: submitjob

    Cooks the current TOP network as a standalone job in a `hython` session on a RunPod pod.

Output Node:
    #id: submitjobnode

    When on, specifies the path to the node to cook. If a node is not specified, the display node of the network that contains the scheduler is cooked instead.

Save Task Graph File:
    #id: submitjobfile

    When on, the submitted job will save a task graph `.py` file once the cook completes.

== Message Queue ==
#id: messagequeue

    The Message Queue (MQ) server is required to get work item results from the jobs running on RunPod pods. The MQ runs locally and communicates with pods via the network.

:include _scheduler_common#mqusage:

:include _scheduler_common#mqaddr:

:include _scheduler_common#taskcallbackport:

:include _scheduler_common#mqrelayport:

== RPC Server ==

Parameters for configuring the behavior of RPC connections from out of process jobs back to a scheduler instance.

